            ("Mistake #1: Building Heat-Neutral 'Mechs", "**The Mistake:**\nNew players often design or choose 'Mechs that can fire all weapons without generating net heat. While this sounds ideal, it's actually suboptimal.\n\n**Why It's Wrong:**\nA truly heat-neutral 'Mech is either under-gunned or under-armored. You've sacrificed firepower or protection to add heat sinks you don't need every turn. Heat should build up each round as you fire your full arsenal.\n\n**The Fix:**\nDesign 'Mechs that run 2-3 heat over dissipation when firing everything. This lets you alpha strike (fire everything) for 3-4 consecutive turns before needing to manage heat. Against opponents, you'll typically destroy them before heat becomes critical. Occasional minor internal damage from overheating costs less than getting hit because you were under-gunned.\n\n**Expert Tip:**\nIn the 3025 era, most 'Mechs should have 10-15 heat sinks. More than that usually means you're wasting tonnage."),
