            ("Mistake #7: Moving Without Gaining Evasion", "**The Mistake:**\nMoving short distances that don't generate evasion pips, thinking any movement is good.\n\n**Why It's Wrong:**\nMovement in BattleTech serves two purposes:\n- Gaining evasion charges (max 4 pips)\n- Positioning\n\nIf you're not gaining evasion AND not improving position, you should BRACE instead for 50% damage reduction.\n\n**The Fix:**\n**Movement Priorities:**\n1. If you can gain evasion: MOVE and maximize pips\n2. If you can't gain evasion but can improve position: MOVE\n3. If neither: BRACE for Bulwark/Vigilance\n\nWasted movement just exposes you to fire without benefit. Better to brace and reduce incoming damage by 50%.\n\n**Jump Jet Advantage:**\nJump jets generate more evasion per hex moved and ignore terrain modifiers. Critical for brawlers."),
